The validation in ValidateWithPath only checks name mismatch if s.Name is not empty. However, this creates an inconsistency: if the name is empty, the function will report "name is required" from v.Validate(), but won't report the directory mismatch. For better error reporting, consider always checking the directory name against the expected value from the path, even when the name field is empty.
